USB POWER SUPPLY SETTING


OptionDescription
ONThe camera draws power from the connected device, reducing the drain on the camera battery.
OFFThe camera does not draw power from the connected device.
Choose whether power is supplied to the camera when it is con-
nected to a computer or other device via a USB cable.

The camera cannot draw power from Lightning connections or from
devices that do not supply power. Select OFF before connecting the
camera to such devices. The connection may not be available for data
transfer or the like when ON is selected.

● The term "draw power" is used when the connected device supplies
power to the camera.
● Regardless of the option chosen, the battery will charge while the
camera is off.

# USB POWER SUPPLY SETTING

Choose whether power is supplied to the camera when it is con-
nected to a computer or other device via a USB cable.

| Option | Description |
| --- | --- |
| ON | The camera draws power from the connected device, reducing the drain on the camera battery. |
| OFF | The camera does not draw power from the connected device. |


The camera cannot draw power from Lightning connections or from
devices that do not supply power. Select OFF before connecting the
camera to such devices. The connection may not be available for data
transfer or the like when ON is selected.

- ● The term "draw power" is used when the connected device supplies
- power to the camera.
- ● Regardless of the option chosen, the battery will charge while the
- camera is off.
